[SN]TITLE[SN]
Murder charge over disabled man Nicholas Churton's death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with murder over the death of a disabled man whose body was found in Wrexham.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Nicholas Anthony Churton, 67, was found dead at an address in Crescent Close at about 08:20 BST on Monday.
North Wales Police said Jordan Davidson will appear before magistrates in the town on Saturday.
The 25-year-old also faces three charges of robbery, two of burglary and offences against police officers.
